ZH: 他从来不撒谎。
EN: He never tells lies.

ZH: 她为了逃避责任而撒谎。
EN: She lied to avoid responsibility.

ZH: 你撒谎的目的是什么？
EN: What is your purpose of lying?

ZH: 孩子撒谎是为了隐藏自己的错误。
EN: Kids lie to cover up their mistakes.

ZH: 如果你撒谎，是很难获得信任的。
EN: It's difficult to gain trust if you lie.

ZH: 他的撒谎被揭穿了。
EN: His lie was exposed.

ZH: 我父母教育我不要撒谎。
EN: My parents taught me not to lie.

ZH: 要坦诚待人，不要撒谎。
EN: Be honest with others, don't lie.

ZH: 别人相信了他的撒谎。
EN: Others believed his lies.

ZH: 撒谎会损害你的信誉。
EN: Lying will damage your reputation.

ZH: 在某些情况下，撒谎可以保护自己。
EN: In certain situations, lying can protect oneself.

ZH: 小孩子常常撒谎来逃避惩罚。
EN: Children often lie to avoid punishment.

ZH: 撒谎是不道德的行为。
EN: Lying is an unethical behavior.

ZH: 我知道你在撒谎，别再瞎编了。
EN: I know you're lying, stop making things up.

ZH: 撒谎让人失去了真实的自我。
EN: Lying makes people lose their true self.

ZH: 不要因为害怕而撒谎。
EN: Don't lie out of fear.

ZH: 他为了保护朋友撒谎了。
EN: He lied to protect his friend.

ZH: 撒谎是一种不负责任的行为。
EN: Lying is an irresponsible act.

ZH: 我们应该避免撒谎的习惯。
EN: We should avoid the habit of lying.

ZH: 别以为撒谎能解决问题。
EN: Don't think that lying can solve problems.

ZH: 撒谎违背了诚实的原则。
EN: Lying goes against the principle of honesty.
